				\begin{document}$${\text{Code:}}\quad {\text{value}} = {\text{analogRead}}\left( {{\text{A}}0} \right);$$\end{document}Because of usage of analogRead(A0) function, the Ardunio reads the voltage applied to the pin A0. Furthermore, this function returns a number between 0 and 1023. As Ardunio Uno R3 uses a 10 bit ATmega microcontroller and 210 = 1024, for this reason the analogRead() function converts the analog signal to a digital signal between 0 and 1023. The voltage sensor of the prototype device is a DIYmall Voltage Sensor DC 0-25 V. This Voltage sensor can detect the supply voltage from 0.0245 to 25 V. Ardunio Uno R3’s Atmega 328 microcontroller operates at 5 V, thus to operate the microcontroller within 5 V the solar panels voltage needs to be reduced (As a solar panel provides 12 V/24 V). The voltage reduction is done with the voltage divider circuitry in cooperated with the voltage sensor module and the following codes has been used.6Code:vin=vout/R2/R1+R2;\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
